package management
rpm - yum


rpm - i = yum install


dependencies


yum search for package anywhere and install it.
Resolves dependencies automatically.

configuration files - one place for all configurations
yum has its own config file

/etc/yum.repos.d/

file:// => file protocol
gpgcheck=0 => disabled; to check digital signature of the software
extension should be .repo


Test your config - > yum repolist

yum ins heavy
yum breaks, performance concerns

dnf is more stable

wget download and install file from URL

fusion is alternate to wget


